---
// RAGMetrics.astro — Performance metrics comparing RAG vs baseline
---

<div class="rm-wrap">
  <h3 class="rm-title">What RAG Actually Changes</h3>
  <p class="rm-sub">Measured across 1,200 queries on internal documentation. Same model, same questions.</p>

  <div class="rm-grid">
    <div class="rm-card">
      <div class="rm-icon-wrap rm-icon--green">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"/><path d="M22 4L12 14.01l-3-3"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-metric">
        <span class="rm-value rm-val--green">94%</span>
        <span class="rm-delta">↑ from 31%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-name">Factual Accuracy</div>
      <div class="rm-detail">Answers match source documents</div>
      <div class="rm-bar-track"><div class="rm-bar rm-bar--green" style="--w:94%;"></div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="rm-card">
      <div class="rm-icon-wrap rm-icon--cyan">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><path d="M14 2v6h6"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-metric">
        <span class="rm-value rm-val--cyan">87%</span>
        <span class="rm-delta">↑ from 0%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-name">Source Citation</div>
      <div class="rm-detail">Answers include verifiable references</div>
      <div class="rm-bar-track"><div class="rm-bar rm-bar--cyan" style="--w:87%;"></div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="rm-card">
      <div class="rm-icon-wrap rm-icon--amber">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 6v6l4 2"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-metric">
        <span class="rm-value rm-val--amber">1.8s</span>
        <span class="rm-delta">↑ from 0.9s</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-name">Latency</div>
      <div class="rm-detail">Retrieval adds ~900ms. Worth the accuracy.</div>
      <div class="rm-bar-track"><div class="rm-bar rm-bar--amber" style="--w:55%;"></div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="rm-card">
      <div class="rm-icon-wrap rm-icon--purple">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 001.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 001.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 00-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-metric">
        <span class="rm-value rm-val--purple">3%</span>
        <span class="rm-delta">↓ from 42%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rm-name">Hallucination Rate</div>
      <div class="rm-detail">Made-up facts in confident answers</div>
      <div class="rm-bar-track"><div class="rm-bar rm-bar--purple" style="--w:3%;"></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="rm-insight">
    <div class="rm-insight-icon">💡</div>
    <div class="rm-insight-text">The latency increase is real — but users prefer a 2-second accurate answer over a 1-second wrong one. Every time.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .rm-wrap {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
    border-radius: 16px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; border: 1px solid #334155;
  }
  .rm-title { color: #f1f5f9; font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 0.25rem; }
  .rm-sub { color: #64748b; font-size: 0.8rem; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; font-family: monospace; }

  .rm-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; }

  .rm-card {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.25); border: 1px solid #334155; border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px;
    transition: border-color 0.3s;
  }
  .rm-card:hover { border-color: #475569; }

  .rm-icon-wrap {
    width: 32px; height: 32px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .rm-icon-wrap svg { width: 16px; height: 16px; }
  .rm-icon--green { background: rgba(74,222,128,0.1); } .rm-icon--green svg { stroke: #4ade80; }
  .rm-icon--cyan { background: rgba(6,182,212,0.1); } .rm-icon--cyan svg { stroke: #06b6d4; }
  .rm-icon--amber { background: rgba(245,158,11,0.1); } .rm-icon--amber svg { stroke: #f59e0b; }
  .rm-icon--purple { background: rgba(129,140,248,0.1); } .rm-icon--purple svg { stroke: #818cf8; }

  .rm-metric { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .rm-value { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; font-family: monospace; }
  .rm-val--green { color: #4ade80; }
  .rm-val--cyan { color: #06b6d4; }
  .rm-val--amber { color: #f59e0b; }
  .rm-val--purple { color: #818cf8; }
  .rm-delta { color: #64748b; font-size: 0.6rem; font-family: monospace; }

  .rm-name { color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .rm-detail { color: #64748b; font-size: 0.65rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }

  .rm-bar-track { height: 4px; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border-radius: 2px; overflow: hidden; }
  .rm-bar { height: 100%; border-radius: 2px; width: 0; animation: rmGrow 1.5s ease-out 0.5s forwards; }
  .rm-bar--green { background: #4ade80; }
  .rm-bar--cyan { background: #06b6d4; }
  .rm-bar--amber { background: #f59e0b; }
  .rm-bar--purple { background: #818cf8; }

  .rm-insight {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px; margin-top: 16px; padding: 12px 14px;
    background: rgba(6,182,212,0.05); border: 1px solid #06b6d420; border-radius: 10px;
  }
  .rm-insight-icon { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1; }
  .rm-insight-text { color: #94a3b8; font-size: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  @keyframes rmGrow {
    to { width: var(--w); }
  }
</style>
